memberdef.name: SdfPathFindPrefixedRange

briefdescription.para: Find the subrange of the sorted range [begin, end) that includes all paths prefixed by path.

detaileddescription.para: The input range must be ordered according to SdfPath::operator<. If your range's iterators' value_types are not SdfPath, but you can obtain SdfPaths from them (e.g. map<SdfPath, X>::iterator), you can pass a function to extract the path from the dereferenced iterator in getPath.

memberdef.name: SdfPathFindLongestPrefix

briefdescription.para: Return an iterator to the element of [begin, end) that is the longest prefix of the given path (including the path itself), if there is such an element, otherwise end.

detaileddescription.para: The input range must be ordered according to SdfPath::operator<. If your range's iterators' value_types are not SdfPath, but you can obtain SdfPaths from them (e.g. vector<pair<SdfPath, X>>::iterator), you can pass a function to extract the path from the dereferenced iterator in getPath.

memberdef.name: SdfPathFindLongestStrictPrefix

briefdescription.para: Return an iterator to the element of [begin, end) that is the longest prefix of the given path (excluding the path itself), if there is such an element, otherwise end.

detaileddescription.para: The input range must be ordered according to SdfPath::operator<. If your range's iterators' value_types are not SdfPath, but you can obtain SdfPaths from them (e.g. vector<pair<SdfPath, X>>::iterator), you can pass a function to extract the path from the dereferenced iterator in getPath.

briefdescription.para: Return an iterator pointing to the element of set whose key is the longest prefix of the given path (including the path itself).

detaileddescription.para: If there is no such element, return set.end().
